---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Advertising Policy - Sojorn" description="How advertising works on Sojorn and what we refuse to do">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-egyptianBlue">Advertising Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: February 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p class="lead font-semibold">We run ads to fund the platform. Here is exactly how they work and everything we refuse to do.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">1. Contextual Only, In-House Only</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">All advertising on Sojorn is served directly by MPLS LLC. We do not use third-party ad networks, demand-side platforms, or programmatic exchanges. No third-party scripts, tracking pixels, or advertising SDKs are embedded in sponsored content.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">2. How Ad Relevance Works</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We do not engage in behavioral targeting. Ads are never selected based on browsing history, message content, or any form of surveillance. Instead, ad relevance is determined by three explicit, user-controlled factors:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Geography</strong> — advertisers select a neighborhood zone or radius, not an audience.</li>
        <li><strong>Content section</strong> — which part of the app the ad appears in (feed, quips, or beacons).</li>
        <li><strong>Interest categories</strong> — you explicitly choose categories you care about (food, events, services, real estate, etc.). Advertisers pick a neighborhood and a category. The match is made on your declared preferences, not on tracked behavior. You can change or clear your preferences at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">A person who says "I care about local restaurants" is a better match for a restaurant ad than someone who got cookied visiting a food blog once. Explicit preference beats surveillance every time.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">3. Full Transparency</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sponsored content is always clearly labeled "Sponsored" or "Promoted" and is never disguised as organic content. Users can tap "Why am I seeing this?" on any sponsored post, which will explain: <em>"This ad is shown because you are in [neighborhood] and selected [category] as an interest. It is not targeted based on your personal data or browsing behavior."</em></p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">4. Same Rules for Everyone</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sponsored content runs through the same AI moderation pipeline and community guidelines as all other content on Sojorn. There are no exceptions for paying advertisers. If sponsored content violates our guidelines, the ad is rejected and the advertiser is refunded.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">5. Data Minimization for Advertisers</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We provide advertisers with aggregate metrics only:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Neighborhood selected</li>
        <li>Total impressions (aggregate)</li>
        <li>Total taps (aggregate)</li>
        <li>Campaign duration</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">That is it. We never share user-level data, demographics, device information, user IDs, or any other identifying information with advertisers.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">6. Prohibited Ad Categories</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">The following categories of advertising are permanently banned from Sojorn:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Alcohol</li>
        <li>Gambling</li>
        <li>Political advertising of any kind</li>
        <li>Surveillance, tracking, or monitoring products</li>
        <li>Law enforcement or government agency promotions</li>
        <li>Data brokers or ad-tech companies</li>
        <li>Anything that contradicts our mission of user privacy and community safety</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">7. User Control</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Users can hide or dismiss any individual sponsored post. We are exploring options for reduced ad frequency or an ad-free experience as a future feature.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">8. Our Commitment</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Advertising exists to sustain the platform, not to exploit the people who use it. We will never build behavioral profiles, sell your attention to the highest bidder, or allow advertisers to track you across the internet. If we ever fail to uphold these commitments, our <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">open-source code</a> is there for anyone to verify.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">9. Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">For advertising inquiries: <a href="mailto:hello@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">hello@sojorn.net</a>.<br>
        For privacy concerns about advertising: <a href="mailto:privacy@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">privacy@sojorn.net</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
